data.responses: {"Q0":"I thought that the remembering of the word at the end was very stupid, the survey itself takes so long and it asks you to remember a lot of things. I honoustly struggled to think off the word at the end."}
{"Q0":"Remembered one room and top of others, then tried to put the words I didnt remember in rooms in same way as the room I remember. Does that make sense?"}

{"Q0":"In some cases I tried to associate the word with where it was.  I also tried to see if they were grouped in any special way, and some seemed to be.  I also said the words aloud in a certain order and tried to remember them."}
{"Q0":"Well, I was definitely surprised at the ones that were 9/9.  Good guesswork in some cases!"}
{"Q0":"I am good at learning the whole scene."}
{"Q0":"I tried to remember the words and placements and sometimes put them into different categories. I looked at the words as belonging together."}
{"Q0":"I used a wide variety of methods"}
{"Q0":"I generally tried to remember the whole scene by grouping words together in my mind so that i could recall them later "}
{"Q0":"I tried to use things in each room to remind me of where the words should go like if most words were one room was mainly clothing I would remember clothing room."}
